=A0
Yes, it is pretty difficult to find materials (including wood =
and ghee) that are "pure". Make your best effort to procure purer materials=
. In the end, when you sit down for homam, pray to Lord to forgive the impu=
rities. In the homam manuals, you will see "gange cha yamune chaiva... amRt=
am bhavatu". Then imagine that water in that glass/bowl/container has becom=
e blessed and pure and sprinkle a bit on yourself and materials. That over =
the time compensates for any impurity and cleanses all. On the material pla=
ne, do your best for material perfection. On the spiritual plane, do your b=
est to increase your faith. Both will hopefully converge oneday..

=A0
The =
simplest abhishek one can do is to take a Shiva Linga and pour water or mil=
k (or whatever materials) while chanting "Om Namah Shivaaya" or any other m=
antras of Shiva. This is safe for anyone to do and remember that Bholenath =
Shiva is easily satisfied and does not require much scholarship and technic=
al prowess, but innocence and faith.
=A0
If one is able to chant namakam an=
d chamakam, one can chant them also. But a simple panchakshari is honestly =
powerful enough for any purpose.

=A0
Everything has been unnecessarily com=
plicated by people of our age. I once read a story. An old brahmin had a ca=
t. He would tie it before doing his daily homam, because the cat might othe=
rwise cause disturbance. A sishya who observed him everyday decided to do a=
 daily homam. He assumed that tying the cat was an essential step. :-) He b=
ought a cat especially for that purpose and tied it away from homa kundam b=
efore homam everyday! His disciples and their disciplies did the same in du=
e course of time. :-)
=A0
Many steps in rituals are kind of like that, i.e.=
 the real purpose of a step is lost and it becomes a redundant/empty/meanin=
gless exercise.
=A0
Second thing is that even some steps that are essential=
 are not exactly followed by people. People read out instructions in Sanskr=
it without *following* them. This is like chanting "take so and so pill for=
 headache" and then moving on, instead of actually taking the pill! :-) For=
 example, many just chant "praaNaanaayamya" and go on with the ritual witho=
ut actually restraining prana. The line means "having restrained the life f=
orce". You are supposed to do praaNaayaama for as long as it takes to disci=
pline the life force and do the rest of the ritual when your breathing is r=
egular and rhythmic and your mind is calm, relaxed and focused.

=A0
